About This Item

Details

  • Features chicken as the first ingredient for a healthy, delicious snack.
  • Grain-free treat made without corn, wheat, soy, or artificial preservatives.
  • Soft bits are ideal for tearing during training.
  • Fresh, oven-baked taste and smell is irresistible to pups.
  • As with all Newman's Own products, 100% of the proceeds go to charity.

See More

Take a break with Newman's Own Snack Sticks and watch your dog dance with joy. These breakable, chewy bits are designed to be the ideal training treat for your furry BFF. Made with farm-raised chicken, every delectable, rip-able bite is free from grains, corn, wheat and soy! Your pup will love to munch on these mouthwatering bits, while you relish that he's snacking on something that's good for him. Plus, it's a Newman's Own product, which means 100% of the proceeds go to charity!

Feeding Instructions

This product is intended for intermittent or supplemental feeding only. Make sure your dog always has fresh water and gets plenty of exercise. Not for human consumption. Store in a cool, dry place.

                          6 Customer Questions

                          Are Newman's Own Dog Treats sourced and made completely in the USA?
                          Answer by • Jul 25, 2019
                          These treats are manufactured in a pet-specialty facility in the United States using ingredients sourced in the US.
                          How long are these? How many in the 5 oz bag/
                          Answer by • May 13, 2019
                          The sticks very in length between 4 and 5 inches. There are approximately 18 treats in each bag.
                          Are these soft? Can I break them apart easily?
                          Answer by • Mar 19, 2021
                          These baked treats are soft and ideal for breaking apart during training.
                          Are newmans heathy dog treats?
                          Answer by • Jan 07, 2022
                          These soft breakable sticks have U.S. farm raised chicken as the #1 ingredient and are free from grains, corn, wheat, soy and artificial preservatives. This product is intended for intermittent or supplemental feeding only. Make sure your dog always has fresh water and gets plenty of exercise.

                          402 Customer Reviews

                          Rated 5 out of 5 stars
                          By CSF on Aug 4, 2023

                          Newman's Own Snack Sticks For Dogs

                          Our 2 rescue Beagle seniors are picky eaters from dry or wet dog food to treats. In addition, they had periondontal disease, resulting in the loss of several teeth. As a result, treats that are easy to chew (soft and/or chewy) are the best. However, taste is also key to their eating/not eating a treat. The snack sticks are easy to break into pieces, are soft and chewy, and are a favorite of our picky eaters. I also applaud that 100% of profits go to charity. It's a win for our senior Beagles and a win for charities.

                          Rated 3 out of 5 stars
                          By AgilityMom on Aug 13, 2023

                          Soft Treats

                          I was looking for some new rewards for my standard poodle, Happy. These were okay. They're soft sticks, which Hap took willingly, but over half of the sticks in the package were broken up. I wouldn't turn them down as a treat, but probably wouldn't buy them again, because there is sooo much else out there.

                          Rated 5 out of 5 stars
                          By Sandy on Aug 8, 2023

                          Great snack!

                          My dog LOVES these - but I make sure to break them into 3 or 4 pieces, because she swallowed the first ones whole and I'm afraid she'd choke on them. They are easy to break into sections. To repeat, she LOVES these treats! I've already purchased more, this time the bigger bag.

                          Rated 5 out of 5 stars
                          By Gusmom on Aug 18, 2023

                          Perfect for training

                          I bought these to try with my large golden doodle who is in agility training. We have strict "no crumbly" treats order. I found them easy to break apart to any size and they don't crumble. My dog loves them. I will definitely order more

                          By Jen on Jun 19, 2023
